			<outline text="July 23" created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 15:13:20 GMT" type="calendarDay" name="23">
				<outline text="I was never that into Van Morrison, but his music fits perfectly with the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/Echo-Studio/dp/B07G9Y3ZMC/ref=asc_df_B07G9Y3ZMC/&quot;&gt;Echo Studio&lt;/a&gt; speaker. I just say &lt;i&gt;Alexa play Van Morrison&lt;/i&gt; and get to writing. " created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 15:32:15 GMT" type="outline"/>
				<outline text="It's bad politics to alienate a whole gender" created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 15:13:21 GMT" type="outline" description="Josh Hawley and the Repubs are onto something. " metaImage="http://scripting.com/images/2022/07/23/hawleyRunning.png">
					<outline text="I hate &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Josh_Hawley&quot;&gt;Hawley&lt;/a&gt; but he's onto &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npr.org/2021/11/11/1054615028/is-masculinity-under-attack-sen-hawley-wants-to-defend-the-men-of-america&quot;&gt;something&lt;/a&gt;.  " created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 15:13:24 GMT"/>
					<outline text="The Dems probably unintentionally do things to push male voters away. He, and the Repubs are milking that for all it's worth. "/>
					<outline text="You can argue the righteousness of it, but it's bad politics to alienate a whole gender. Bad for winning elections, assuming that's what the Dems want to do. " created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 15:16:00 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Also by making him &lt;a href=&quot;https://trends.google.com/trends/explore?q=hawley&amp;geo=US&quot;&gt;famous&lt;/a&gt; you're helping him, even if you say nasty shit about him. " created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 15:17:42 GMT"/>
					<outline text="Ask &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/GeorgeLakoff&quot;&gt;George Lakoff&lt;/a&gt;. People don't care whether you &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.axios.com/2021/11/07/josh-hawley-masculinity-porn-video-games&quot;&gt;like him&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.rollingstone.com/politics/politics-news/josh-hawley-masculinity-obsession-1254776/&quot;&gt;not&lt;/a&gt;, but when you push him, you're creating a bigger space in their minds labeled X where X is the name of the asshole you're writing about. " created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 15:19:10 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I'm doing it right now, I know it -- can't think of a way of avoiding it and still make the point." created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 15:19:47 GMT"/>
					<outline text="I bet the Dems could pick up 10% more male voters just by doing a little marketing saying the Dems care. " created="Sat, 23 Jul 2022 15:19:55 GMT"/>
					</outline>
