				<outline text="Which Markdown?" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 13:52:14 GMT" type="outline" description="The approach we all take with Markdown text is to stay within a reasonable subset of the syntax, and hope for the best. ðŸ˜€">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scripting/reallysimple/discussions/6#discussioncomment-3187614&quot;&gt;Joseph Zitt&lt;/a&gt;: &quot;It's very cool that you're supporting Markdown -- but which Markdown are you using?&quot;" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 13:52:19 GMT"/>
					<outline text="This of course is a great question. I answered it, the way all Markdown questions are answered. " created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 13:52:42 GMT">
						<outline text="Of course as you know there is no One True Markdown." created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 13:53:09 GMT"/>
						<outline text="The approach we all take with Markdown text is to stay within a reasonable subset of the syntax, and hope for the best. ;-)" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 13:53:19 GMT"/>
						<outline text="I go by this &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.markdownguide.org/cheat-sheet/&quot;&gt;cheat sheet&lt;/a&gt;, which I keep in an icon in the chrome of my browser, easy to reach for. And it seems to work." created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 13:53:36 GMT"/>
						<outline text="Re the Markdown processors I use --" created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 13:53:49 GMT" flBulletedSubs="true">
							<outline text="On the client side -- I use &lt;a href=&quot;http://fargo.io/code/markdownConverter.js&quot;&gt;something&lt;/a&gt; called MarkdownCoverter, which I downloaded many years ago. I seem to recall it's the one that StackExchange uses, so I figured it's got to be pretty good. In all the years I've been using it there haven't been any complaints as far as I know." created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 13:53:47 GMT"/>
							<outline text="On the server side -- I use &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npmjs.com/package/marked&quot;&gt;markd&lt;/a&gt;. I don't recall how I decided to use this one, but it has also served me well." created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 13:53:47 GMT"/>
							</outline>
						<outline text="As I understand it Gruber likes the way it has evolved. " created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 13:53:16 GMT"/>
						<outline text="The shit does kind of hit the fan when it comes to using Markdown in something like RSS where interop is the primary thing. " created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 14:46:47 GMT"/>
						<outline text="But this was one of the first enhancements I wanted to get out there in 2022, the 20th year of RSS 2.0." created="Wed, 20 Jul 2022 14:47:03 GMT"/>
